<Base title="A View of One's Own. Paulina Stasik — Michalina Sablik">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h1>A View of One's Own. Paulina Stasik</h1>
    <p class="exhibition-detail-venue">BWA Tarnów | 2025</p>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-body">
      <p>The exhibition features paintings and works on paper by Kraków-based artist Paulina Stasik. Her work combines allegory and symbolism with autobiographical elements, forming "an intimate, yet camouflaged, self-portrait over time." At age 35, the artist explores a transitional moment—positioned between past and future.</p>
      <p>The exhibition examines her artistic journey through childhood, maturation, embodied memory, and formative relationships. Stasik deliberately engages with traditional iconographic models of "stages of a woman's life" from medieval through 19th-century art, consciously challenging patriarchal assumptions by depicting self-discovery and agency rather than passive social roles.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-credits">
      <p><strong>Curator:</strong> Michalina Sablik</p>
      <p><strong>Photographs:</strong> Szymon Sokołowski</p>
      <p><strong>Companion book:</strong> "Self-Portrait with Tongue Sticking Out" designed by Agata Biskup</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-gallery" style="margin-top: 2.5rem; display: grid; gap: 1rem;">
